:boundaryLayerDragAssertion a :Cl_BoundaryLayerAssertion ;
    :sourcePage :chapter4SourcePage ;
    :mentions :Cl_BoundaryLayer , :Cl_Wing , :Cl_Friction , :Cl_Viscosity , :Cl_Drag ;
    :hasTextValue "Once the boundary layer of the air adheres to the wing by friction, further resistance to the airflow is caused by the viscosity ... When these two forces act together to resist airflow over a wing, it is called drag." .
